      "description": "This 2004 Carrera 4S is an impeccable example of the wide-body 996 chassis. Power is delivered via a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six featuring a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The 6-speed manual gearbox offers precise engagement through a factory short-shift kit. Mechanically, the vehicle is superlative: the suspension geometry remains true to factory specs, and the Brembo four-piston monoblock calipers provide immediate, fade-free deceleration. The Arctic Silver metallic finish retains original paint depth, and the Metropol Blue leather interior shows zero bolster compression. A true collector-grade specimen with a fully documented service dossier.",
